There was wide jubilation in Abigborodo Community in Warri North Local Government Area of Delta State State as Dr. Emmanuel Ewetan Uduaghan, former Governor of the State officially rejoined the People’s Democratic Party, PDP from the All Progressives Congress. The indigenes of Abigborodo Community were seen dancing for the return of the former Governor to the Party. Dr. Uduaghan rejoined the PDP from Unit 1, Ward 6 in Abigborodo Community. This former Governor was accompanied by Hon. Thomas Ereyitomi, member representing Warri Federal Constituency as well as the Peoples Democratic Party’s PDP Deputy Chairman(Delta South), Mr. Ada-Val Areyenka to his community.